name: Version 2.1.0
body:
- @henryli17 fixed issue #12 which showcased a rare bug where the album API responds with `{'albums': []}` as opposed to `{}` which caused a `KeyError`
- Fixed issue with Pillow unsupported files based on the issue report and solution discussed with @Snuggle

name: Version 2.0.6
body: Fix the bug that I caused where sanitizing the album comes before checking if the album actually has a title causing a key error.

name: Version 2.0.5
body: Merged pull from @Snuggle with a fix for the MediaItems key error.

name: Version 2.0.3
body: Fixed a bug where all items in an album are already present in another album causing the program to crash.

name: Version 2.0.1
body:
Added debugging mode -d --debugging

Fixed the bug where mediaItems key wasn't found.

name: gparch_cli
body:
Features Added:
- Multithreaded downloading
- Album/Shared Album/Favorites Support
- Automatic library updating
- CLI Interface
- Color text interface

There is an executable version of this script targeted for 64-bit Windows.

If you are just using python, download the source code to run.
